===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|sunne|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|sunnōn}} (compare West Frisian {{term|sinne|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|zon}}, German {{term|Sonne|lang=de}}), from [[heteroclitic]] [[inanimate]] {{proto|Indo-European|sóh₂wl̥}}. 'sun' (compare Welsh {{term|huan|lang=cy}} / {{term|haul|lang=cy}}, Avestan gen. ''x<sup>v</sup>əng''), genitive of *''séh₂wl''. More at {{term|solar|lang=en}} and at Icelandic {{term|sunna|lang=is}}.

